FINAL REPORT EXAMINATION: Chest radiograph
INDICATION: Dyspnea.
TECHNIQUE: AP and lateral views of the chest.
COMPARISON: ___
FINDINGS:
Heart size is mildly enlarged. There is mild unfolding of the thoracic aorta. Cardiomediastinal silhouette and hilar contours are otherwise unremarkable. There is mild bibasilar atelectasis. Lungs are otherwise clear. Pleural surfaces are clear without effusion or pneumothorax. Focus of air seen under the right hemidiaphragm, likely represents colonic interposition.
IMPRESSION:
No acute cardiopulmonary abnormality.
